Let's have some fun. We play the game "Keep talking and nobody explodes together"



Keep talking and nobody explodes:

You’re alone in a room with a bomb. Your friends, the “Experts”, have the manual needed to defuse it. But there’s a catch: the Experts can’t see the bomb, so everyone will need to talk it out – fast!

Put your puzzle-solving and communication skills to the test as you and your friends race to defuse bombs quickly before time runs out!

URL: https://keeptalkinggame.com/


Please note, this is a fun activity which is completely optional for you to join. This is a game which requires team work and collaboration to diffuse a bomb.

One person is diffusing the bomb, while the rest of the team is guiding the person to diffuse the bomb. As the person diffusing you do not know how to diffuse the bomb and you need to give your peers hints on what the bomb is. The other people have instructions on how to diffuse the bomb, but do not see the bomb itself.


This is a bit of an experiment to get us together and have some fun together.

Please RSVP until Tuesday EOD. We will be playing in groups of 5-8 people and I need to make sure I have enough copies of the game. We need to have 1 copy of the game per group. Please send me a HIVE message if you already have a copy of the game and you want to participate.

Let's have some fun. We play the game "Keep talking and nobody explodes together"



Keep talking and nobody explodes:

You’re alone in a room with a bomb. Your friends, the “Experts”, have the manual needed to defuse it. But there’s a catch: the Experts can’t see the bomb, so everyone will need to talk it out – fast!

Put your puzzle-solving and communication skills to the test as you and your friends race to defuse bombs quickly before time runs out!

URL: https://keeptalkinggame.com/


Please note, this is a fun activity which is completely optional for you to join. This is a game which requires team work and collaboration to diffuse a bomb.

One person is diffusing the bomb, while the rest of the team is guiding the person to diffuse the bomb. As the person diffusing you do not know how to diffuse the bomb and you need to give your peers hints on what the bomb is. The other people have instructions on how to diffuse the bomb, but do not see the bomb itself.


This is a bit of an experiment to get us together and have some fun together.

Please RSVP until Tuesday EOD. We will be playing in groups of 5-8 people and I need to make sure I have enough copies of the game. We need to have 1 copy of the game per group. Please send me a HIVE message if you already have a copy of the game and you want to participate.


The Game to download (if you want to play defuser):

https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1HURfDnjj56qmGD0GmzfUPdOnW7lO5iA1?usp=sharing


The Manual (For everyone):

Please download the manual (for best experience, print out the manual)

https://drive.google.com/file/d/1krtvgOq457C1xISKG5xiAdVp7MhVRFRH/view?usp=sharing

Dear all,

This is the invitation to discuss the Teams App integration opportunity with the Beekeeper Team.
Goal of the call is to get to know each other, for the Beekeeper team to understand what we offer and how we position the Teams platform and last but not least to align on possible next steps.
Feel free to forward the invitation accordingly. @Urs Briner<mailto:urs.briner@verve-capital.com> you are warmly welcome to join if the discussion is interesting for you.


High level agenda

  *   Quick introduction of all participants
  *   The MS Teams platform strategy
  *   App integration opportunity and program we offer
  *   Top of mind Beekeeper and questions
  *   Next steps


Looking forward to meet you all together virtually next week.
Kind regards,
Stefanie

Dear All

You are required to attend only 1 of any of these 4 events scheduled annually (Calendar Year), that best fits your availability. The sessions are scheduled in the last month of every quarter. Background information on this requirement, is provided below. I look forward to welcoming you to this General Training on Privacy and Security Session for 2020 and beyond.

Thx
Amir

Background:

One of the outcomes of our Certification audit and a point which all our Customers request evidence for its implementation is training and awareness of all employees. Our Training Policy is implemented by the People team so that every new Bee must complete our online standard training session on Information Security, and some teams compliment this online training with their own monthly specialised sessions (eg OWASP for the engineers).
Although, our Auditors welcomed the initiative of engineering, they have reached the conclusion that the majority of the existing employees may not be sufficiently trained in new/updated topics in the area of Data Privacy and Information Security. 
Therefore, R&C will start offering these sessions to address this requirement for our Certification. Respectively, one topic will be concentrated on and presented, discussed, Q&A, etc. in these sessions. Any remaining time will be allocated to any general discussions and or Q&A with R&C on Data Privacy / Information Security.

SUMMARY: Product & Value Delivery: Show; Not Tell

DESCRIPTION:
The Show; Not Tell (Sprint Review) is an informal meeting which the entire engine attends. The swarms give a demo on the product changes and can receive feedback from other swarm members. Participants outside of the engine are invited to view the progress on the items that are being worked on.

The purpose of the meeting is for the team to show the stakeholders the work they have accomplished over the sprint and compare it to the commitment given at the beginning of the sprint

Note:
Everyone in the company is invited to this event. For people outside the Product & Value delivery engine, this meeting is entirely optional. We welcome anyone to see what we have worked on and what we want to share.


Note 2:
It is not possible to mark the invite for a group as optional. Therefore, in the invite, you may be as required, but if you are not part of the engine, this meeting is optional

Dear All

You are required to attend only 1 of any of these 4 events scheduled annually (Calendar Year), that best fits your availability. The sessions are scheduled in the last month of every quarter. Background information on this requirement, is provided below. I look forward to welcoming you to this General Training on Privacy and Security Session for 2020 and beyond.

Thx
Amir

Background:

One of the outcomes of our Certification audit and a point which all our Customers request evidence for its implementation is training and awareness of all employees. Our Training Policy is implemented by the People team so that every new Bee must complete our online standard training session on Information Security, and some teams compliment this online training with their own monthly specialised sessions (eg OWASP for the engineers).
Although, our Auditors welcomed the initiative of engineering, they have reached the conclusion that the majority of the existing employees may not be sufficiently trained in new/updated topics in the area of Data Privacy and Information Security. 
Therefore, R&C will start offering these sessions to address this requirement for our Certification. Respectively, one topic will be concentrated on and presented, discussed, Q&A, etc. in these sessions. Any remaining time will be allocated to any general discussions and or Q&A with R&C on Data Privacy / Information Security.

DESCRIPTION:
The Show; Not Tell (Sprint Review) is an informal meeting which the entire engine attends. The swarms give a demo on the product changes and can receive feedback from other swarm members. Participants outside of the engine are invited to view the progress on the items that are being worked on.

The purpose of the meeting is for the team to show the stakeholders the work they have accomplished over the sprint and compare it to the commitment given at the beginning of the sprint

Note:
Everyone in the company is invited to this event. For people outside the Product & Value delivery engine, this meeting is entirely optional. We welcome anyone to see what we have worked on and what we want to share.


Note 2:
It is not possible to mark the invite for a group as optional. Therefore, in the invite, you may be as required, but if you are not part of the engine, this meeting is optional

SUMMARY: Product & Value Delivery: Show; Not Tell

DESCRIPTION:
The Show; Not Tell (Sprint Review) is an informal meeting which the entire engine attends. The swarms give a demo on the product changes and can receive feedback from other swarm members. Participants outside of the engine are invited to view the progress on the items that are being worked on.

The purpose of the meeting is for the team to show the stakeholders the work they have accomplished over the sprint and compare it to the commitment given at the beginning of the sprint

Note:
Everyone in the company is invited to this event. For people outside the Product & Value delivery engine, this meeting is entirely optional. We welcome anyone to see what we have worked on and what we want to share.


Note 2:
It is not possible to mark the invite for a group as optional. Therefore, in the invite, you may be as required, but if you are not part of the engine, this meeting is optional

Dear All

You are required to attend only 1 of any of these 4 events scheduled annually (Calendar Year), that best fits your availability. The sessions are scheduled in the last month of every quarter. Background information on this requirement, is provided below. I look forward to welcoming you to this General Training on Privacy and Security Session for 2020 and beyond.

Thx
Amir

Background:

One of the outcomes of our Certification audit and a point which all our Customers request evidence for its implementation is training and awareness of all employees. Our Training Policy is implemented by the People team so that every new Bee must complete our online standard training session on Information Security, and some teams compliment this online training with their own monthly specialised sessions (eg OWASP for the engineers).
Although, our Auditors welcomed the initiative of engineering, they have reached the conclusion that the majority of the existing employees may not be sufficiently trained in new/updated topics in the area of Data Privacy and Information Security. 
Therefore, R&C will start offering these sessions to address this requirement for our Certification. Respectively, one topic will be concentrated on and presented, discussed, Q&A, etc. in these sessions. Any remaining time will be allocated to any general discussions and or Q&A with R&C on Data Privacy / Information Security.

Please note, this is a fully optional event. If you prefer not to take part in quarantine roulette, please feel free to decline the event.

FORMAT US TEAM:
1. FOCUS: ONE focus item for the day (this does not include meetings or ad-hoc, normal day to day tasks)

3. INTERESTING: This could be either personal or about a meet-up, an interesting Ted talk etc

Dear All

You are required to attend only 1 of any of these 4 events scheduled annually (Calendar Year), that best fits your availability. The sessions are scheduled in the last month of every quarter. Background information on this requirement, is provided below. I look forward to welcoming you to this General Training on Privacy and Security Session for 2020 and beyond.

Thx
Amir

Background:

One of the outcomes of our Certification audit and a point which all our Customers request evidence for its implementation is training and awareness of all employees. Our Training Policy is implemented by the People team so that every new Bee must complete our online standard training session on Information Security, and some teams compliment this online training with their own monthly specialised sessions (eg OWASP for the engineers).
Although, our Auditors welcomed the initiative of engineering, they have reached the conclusion that the majority of the existing employees may not be sufficiently trained in new/updated topics in the area of Data Privacy and Information Security. 
Therefore, R&C will start offering these sessions to address this requirement for our Certification. Respectively, one topic will be concentrated on and presented, discussed, Q&A, etc. in these sessions. Any remaining time will be allocated to any general discussions and or Q&A with R&C on Data Privacy / Information Security.

SUMMARY: Product & Value Delivery: Show; Not Tell

DESCRIPTION:
The Show; Not Tell (Sprint Review) is an informal meeting which the entire engine attends. The swarms give a demo on the product changes and can receive feedback from other swarm members. Participants outside of the engine are invited to view the progress on the items that are being worked on.

The purpose of the meeting is for the team to show the stakeholders the work they have accomplished over the sprint and compare it to the commitment given at the beginning of the sprint

Note:
Everyone in the company is invited to this event. For people outside the Product & Value delivery engine, this meeting is entirely optional. We welcome anyone to see what we have worked on and what we want to share.


Note 2:
It is not possible to mark the invite for a group as optional. Therefore, in the invite, you may be as required, but if you are not part of the engine, this meeting is optional

The Show; Not Tell (Sprint Review) is an informal meeting which the entire engine attends. The swarms give a demo on the product changes and can receive feedback from other swarm members. Participants outside of the engine are invited to view the progress on the items that are being worked on.

The purpose of the meeting is for the team to show the stakeholders the work they have accomplished over the sprint and compare it to the commitment given at the beginning of the sprint

Note:
Everyone in the company is invited to this event. For people outside the Product & Value delivery engine, this meeting is entirely optional. We welcome anyone to see what we have worked on and what we want to share.


Note 2:
It is not possible to mark the invite for a group as optional. Therefore, in the invite, you may be as required, but if you are not part of the engine, this meeting is optional
